{# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   7. FAQ — Editorial accordion
   ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ #}
<section class="ep-faq">
  <div class="ep-faq-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">Estate Planning FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">Learn how to protect your legacy and minimize taxes for your heirs.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-ghost">Ask About Estate Planning</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Do you draft wills and trusts? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>No, we don't practice law. We coordinate with estate planning attorneys to ensure your legal documents align with your financial strategy. We'll refer you to a qualified attorney and work with them to implement the plan.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Should I convert my IRA to a Roth for my heirs? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Often, yes. Inherited traditional IRAs are now subject to the 10-year rule, which can push heirs into high tax brackets. Converting to a Roth during your lifetime (when you control the timing and tax impact) can save your heirs tens of thousands in taxes. We model this scenario as part of your estate plan.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What's a Qualified Charitable Distribution (QCD)? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>A QCD allows you to donate up to $105,000 per year directly from your IRA to charity (after age 70½). The distribution counts toward your RMD but doesn't increase your taxable income — a powerful strategy for reducing taxes and supporting causes you care about.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">When should I update my estate plan? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Review your estate plan annually and update it after major life events like marriage, divorce, births, deaths, significant asset changes, or moves to a different state. We conduct an annual beneficiary audit for all clients to ensure your designations still match your intentions.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What happens without an estate plan? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Without an estate plan, state law decides who gets your assets, courts appoint guardians for minor children, and your family may face lengthy probate processes and unnecessary taxes. Proper planning ensures your wishes are honored and your loved ones are protected.</p></div>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

